The thief has now started to change its behavior, turning to&nbsp;Russian crypto exchange <a href="https://www.theblock.co/linked/140739/us-sanctions-worlds-largest-darknet-market-and-linked-russian-crypto-exchange" data-v-f87c67ca="">Garantex</a>&nbsp;to launder the assets. <br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The U.S. government linked the Lazarus Group to the high-profile Ronin exploit that resulted in <a href="https://www.theblock.co/linked/141985/us-government-connects-north-korean-hacking-group-with-last-months-600-million-ronin-exploit" data-v-f87c67ca="">$600 million</a> worth of digital assets being stolen from the <a href="https://www.theblock.co/post/231119/axie-infinity-origins-crypto-game-apple-app-store" data-v-f87c67ca="">Axie Infinity</a> sidechain. In all, Elliptic estimates the Lazarus Group has pilfered more than $2 billion in digital assets across numerous heists.&nbsp;
